author: Aap
title: Woman crashes car after passenger allegedly tried to strangle her - Yahoo7
text:
Share Woman crashes car after passenger allegedly tried to strangle her - Yahoo7 A man allegedly tried to strangle a woman while she was driving causing her to crash her car into a ute. Close VIDEO News break – February 25. Source: 7 News News break – February 25 
The 22-year-old female was taken to hospital with serious injuries after the crash at Stafford, in Brisbane's north, last Sunday, police say. 
The 23-year-old passenger will face the Brisbane Magistrates Court on Saturday morning on a string of charges including strangulation, dangerous interference of a motor vehicle causing grievous bodily harm and deprivation of liberty. 
National domestic violence helpline: 1800 737 732 or 1800RESPECT. In an emergency call triple-zero.
